    <chapter title="Online Dashboard" id="online">
        <p>ANSS uses v10 of Fauna which can display current records and collections on it's <a
                href="https://dashboard.fauna.com/">dashboard</a></p>
        <tip>Login credentials for Fauna are necessary to access the dashboard. If you do not have them, you can contact
            the administrator for assistance.
        </tip>
    </chapter>

    <chapter title="Staff Dashboard" id="staff">
        <p>The staff portal of the website <a href="https://anss.org">anss.org</a> offers a more readable and limited
            view
            to the stored data. And depending on your role and permissions provides a more or less restricted view and
            access to information.</p>
    </chapter>

    <chapter title="Db Shell" id="dbshell">
        <p>Fauna also provides an interactive shell to query from their database using FQL.</p>
    </chapter>

    <chapter title="Api" id="api">
        <p>Several client-drivers (SDKs) and API endpoints are available to query, create, and manipulate data from the
            database. The remainder of this documentation will have a focus on using Fauna's APIs to interact with the
            database.</p>
    </chapter>

</topic>